{
  "stem": "20089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's actually a very, very important part of my whole relationship with-- with Miss Richman, with Abram with Andy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Andy, as a transport officer, always helped Abram with the transport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Miss Richman instructed Andy to provide transport for children whose parents were in Poland, and whose parents requested that the children go back to-- to-- to them in Poland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my instructions from Miss Richman was that she had received from the Red Cross a list of names of children whose parents were in Poland and who were resident in Rosenheim.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had to collect the children and instruct them and the madrichim that the following day, we would transport back-- transport them back to the borders.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at the border, the Red Cross would take the children back to the parents and their homes in Poland.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as a social worker, it was very important for me to reunite family because that's-- that was one of the aspects that I was trained.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One of the most important part of social work is to reunite families and to make them as stable and as well adjusted as possible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Where children are separated from their parents, one expects problems.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so with the instructions from Miss Richman, I got hold of all the children and told all the madrichim that they must be ready the following morning, that they were going to be taken back to their parents.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I actually didn't speak to the children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I spoke only to the madrichim who would accompany them to the border.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And everything was arranged.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Andy had the trucks all ready.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Miss Richman had arranged for food for the trucks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had a party that night.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
